    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_62839330" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/62839330" />
    <a title="Heather Twidle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2496425-heather-twidle"><img alt="Heather Twidle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1246975969p2/2496425.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/62839330?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heather Twidle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heather Twidle" href="/user/show/2496425-heather-twidle">Heather Twidle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780586066232" href="/book/show/991990.The_Songs_Of_Distant_Earth">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer62839330" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15042276746994702941">Sci-fi lit geeks tend, I&apos;ve learned, to fall into one of two categories: Asimov fans, or Clarke fans. I loved the Foundation trilogy as a kid, but this simple novel - even with its fairly bland characters - was so delicate and sad that it launched me firmly into the Clarke camp, and not just because there was a pony in it.</span>
  <span id="freeText15042276746994702941" style="display:none">Sci-fi lit geeks tend, I've learned, to fall into one of two categories: Asimov fans, or Clarke fans. I loved the Foundation trilogy as a kid, but this simple novel - even with its fairly bland characters - was so delicate and sad that it launched me firmly into the Clarke camp, and not just because there was a pony in it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15042276746994702941" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


